President Obama granted clemency to twenty-one individuals, consisting of eight commutations and thirteen pardons. The commutations included individuals convicted of various drug offenses, such as possession and distribution of cocaine and cocaine base. Their prison sentences were commuted to expire on April 17, 2014. The pardons were granted to individuals convicted of offenses including conspiracy to possess and distribute heroin, possession with intent to distribute cocaine base, and armed bank robbery. These individuals had already served their sentences or were given probation.